30/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov has awarded the highest state honour, the Stara Planina Order, to ethnic Turkish political leader Ahmet Dogan. 
He leads the Movement for Rights and Freedoms, which is a minor government partner. 
Parvanov cited Dogan's contribution to the preservation of ethnic peace and tolerance in Bulgaria, saying he went beyond ethnic interests and devoted himself to the future and prosperity of the country. 
(24 Chasa, Trud - 30/03/04; Mediapool - 29/03/04)
